# Cursor Rules for Media Ingest Tool

## Architecture Rules

This project must follow the modular architecture defined in:

* media_ingest_spec.txt
* media_ingest_sdd.txt
* implementation_plan.txt

The system must remain modular.

Do NOT collapse modules into a single file.

---

## Project Structure

The project structure must remain:

media_ingest/
cli.py
pipeline.py
scanner.py
hashing.py
metadata.py
organizer.py
database.py
utils.py

Responsibilities:

cli.py
Command line interface.

pipeline.py
Orchestrates ingest pipeline.

scanner.py
Filesystem scanning.

hashing.py
Content hashing.

metadata.py
Metadata extraction.

database.py
SQLite access layer.

organizer.py
Archive path creation.

utils.py
Shared helpers.

---

## Module Boundaries

Each module must have a single responsibility.

Allowed dependencies:

pipeline → scanner
pipeline → hashing
pipeline → metadata
pipeline → organizer
pipeline → database

scanner must NOT depend on other modules.

database must NOT depend on pipeline.

metadata must remain independent.

---

## File Processing Rules

The ingest pipeline must:

* stream files using generators
* never load the entire file list into memory
* support extremely large archives

Correct pattern:

for path in scan():
process(path)

Incorrect pattern:

files = list(scan())

---

## Duplicate Detection

Duplicates are detected using:

BLAKE3 content hashing.

Hashing must read files in chunks to support large video files.

Never load entire files into memory.

---

## Metadata Extraction

Primary metadata extraction must use:

ExifTool.

Fallback method:

filesystem modification time.

Metadata normalization must produce:

Python datetime objects.

---

## Archive Structure

Files must be organized as:

archive/
YYYY/
MM/
DD/

Directories must be created automatically.

Filename conflicts must be resolved by incrementing suffix numbers.

Example:

photo.jpg
photo_1.jpg
photo_2.jpg

---

## Database Rules

SQLite database must store:

files(
hash TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
path TEXT,
size INTEGER
)

Database code must exist only inside database.py.

Other modules must never execute raw SQL.

---

## Performance Rules

The system must scale to millions of files.

Requirements:

* streaming pipeline
* parallel worker pool
* chunked hashing
* minimal memory usage

Avoid unnecessary disk access.

---

## Code Quality

Follow these conventions:

* Python 3.11+
* type hints for public functions
* descriptive variable names
* small functions
* docstrings for modules

Prefer readability over cleverness.

---

## Error Handling

The pipeline must:

* log errors
* continue processing remaining files
* never crash entire ingest job due to a single file.

---

## AI Generation Rules

When generating code:

* follow the architecture strictly
* update only relevant modules
* avoid duplicating logic
* avoid creating new modules unless necessary

Always maintain modular separation.

---

## Testing

When adding new functionality:

generate tests in:

tests/

Use pytest.

---

## Goal

Maintain a scalable, maintainable media ingest system suitable for very large archives.
